other_tests.findings: Opening pressure was 23 cm of water; CSF was colorless; normal glucose and total protein levels; total nucleated-cell count was 1 per microliter; red-cell count was 61 per microliter; moderate amount of mononuclear cells and rare polymorphonucleocytes on Gram's stain.
Mildly enlarged kidneys with normal parenchymal echotexture; multiple simple-appearing cysts in the left kidney.
Left ventricular ejection fraction of 66% with no valvular abnormalities.
Grossly purulent material aspirated from the lesion; pathological examination revealed debris with abundant neutrophils and fungal hyphae.
